President Trump welcomed Pastor Andrew Brunson and other survivors of religious persecution to the White House. He emphasized the importance of religious liberty and the need to defend and promote it worldwide. The President mentioned that his administration hosted the world's first-ever meeting of foreign ministers dedicated to international religious freedom. He also thanked Ambassador-at-Large for International Religious Freedom Sam Brownback and Pastor Paula White for their efforts in supporting religious freedom. The President heard from individuals representing different religious traditions who shared stories of persecution and the need for assistance. The topics discussed included the persecution of Christians in Pakistan, the situation of the Rohingya people in Bangladesh, the persecution of the Uighur population in China, and the plight of the Yazidi community in Iraq. The President assured the attendees that he would take action and raise their concerns with the relevant authorities.